# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GoStack Environment Configuration Template
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Purpose:
# This file is the canonical reference template for all environment variables
# consumed by a GoStack application. Copy this file to `.env` in your project
# root and fill in the values appropriate for your environment before booting
# the application.
#
# Philosophy:
# Environment configuration must live outside source code. Secrets (passwords,
# API keys, tokens) must never be committed to version control. This file
# contains only safe placeholder values — the real `.env` is listed in
# `.gitignore` and never leaves the host machine.
#
# Architecture:
# At boot, the application calls `gostack.InitConfig(".env")`, which invokes
# `config.Manager.Load()` to parse this file into an in-memory key/value map.
# All framework subsystems (database, mail, session, auth) read from that map.
# Application code may query any key via `gostack.Config.Get("KEY")`.
#
# Choice:
# We use a plain KEY=VALUE format (compatible with bash export syntax) over
# TOML/YAML/JSON to maximise portability across CI systems, Docker, and PaaS
# platforms (Railway, Fly.io, Heroku) that inject environment natively.
#
# Implementation:
# - Lines beginning with '#' are comments and are ignored by the parser.
# - Blank lines are ignored.
# - Values may optionally be wrapped in double or single quotes.
# - Inline comments are supported: KEY=value # this is ignored
# - The parser is implemented in framework/config/config.go (Manager.Load).
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ─── Application ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# APP_NAME: Human-readable name of the application.
# Used in email subjects, log prefixes, and UI titles.
APP_NAME=GoStack

# APP_ENV: The runtime environment. Controls error verbosity and caching.
# Accepted values: local | staging | production
APP_ENV=local

# APP_DEBUG: Whether to expose detailed error traces in HTTP responses.
# Set to false in production to prevent leaking internals to clients.
# Accepted values: true | false
APP_DEBUG=true

# APP_KEY: A 32-character random secret used for session signing and CSRF tokens.
# Generate one with: openssl rand -hex 16
# CAUTION: Changing this in production invalidates all active sessions.
APP_KEY=


# ─── Server ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# APP_PORT: The TCP port the HTTP server listens on.
# Default: 8080
APP_PORT=8080


# ─── Database ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# DB_DRIVER: The database engine to connect to.
# Accepted values: mysql | postgres
DB_DRIVER=mysql

# DB_HOST: Hostname or IP address of the database server.
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1

# DB_PORT: TCP port the database server listens on.
# MySQL default: 3306 | PostgreSQL default: 5432
DB_PORT=3306

# DB_DATABASE: The name of the target database schema.
DB_DATABASE=gostack

# DB_USERNAME: The database user account GoStack connects as.
DB_USERNAME=root

# DB_PASSWORD: Password for DB_USERNAME.
# CAUTION: Never commit a real password. Use a secret manager in production.
DB_PASSWORD=


# ─── Session ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SESSION_LIFETIME: How many minutes a session cookie remains valid.
# After this period the user is automatically signed out.
# Default: 120 (2 hours)
SESSION_LIFETIME=120

# SESSION_COOKIE: The name of the session cookie sent to the browser.
# Default: gostack_session
SESSION_COOKIE=gostack_session


# ─── Mail / SMTP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# MAIL_HOST: Hostname of the SMTP relay server.
# For local development, use Mailtrap (smtp.mailtrap.io) or Mailpit (localhost).
MAIL_HOST=smtp.mailtrap.io

# MAIL_PORT: SMTP port.
# Common values: 25 (plain), 465 (SSL), 587 (STARTTLS — recommended)
MAIL_PORT=587

# MAIL_USERNAME: SMTP authentication username.
MAIL_USERNAME=

# MAIL_PASSWORD: SMTP authentication password.
# CAUTION: Never commit a real credential. Use a secret manager in production.
MAIL_PASSWORD=

# MAIL_ENCRYPTION: Transport security protocol for the SMTP connection.
# Accepted values: tls | ssl | none
MAIL_ENCRYPTION=tls

# MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS: The envelope sender address for all outgoing mail.
MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=hello@example.com

# MAIL_FROM_NAME: The display name shown to recipients in the From header.
MAIL_FROM_NAME="${APP_NAME}"
